<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 4:28AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow along the divide this morning...
Periods of light snow will affect areas along the divide this
morning. This include locations along Highway 2 over Marias Pass
and Highway 200 over Rogers Pass.
Visibility could fall below one half mile at times and roadways
could become snow covered and slippery for a time this morning.
After 10 AM, snowfall will generally melt on pavement surfaces.
Overall snow accumulations will generally range from 1 to 3 inches
at pass level to about 3 to 6 inches at ridge tops.</description>
